org.jscripter.emu.java.lang
Interface Comparable<T>

All Known Implementing Classes:
Boolean, Character, Double, Enum, Float, Integer, Long, Short, String
public interface Comparable<T>

Internally imposes a total ordering on the objects of each class that implements it, emulating a standard java.lang interface or class with the same simple name as this one. This ordering is referred to as the class's natural ordering, and the class's compareTo(Object) method is referred to as its natural comparison method.

This interface or class is only used internally by JS re-compiler implementations.

Please refer to the Java API Standards for detail description of the original class or interface.

Author:
J.J.Liu (Jianjun Liu) at http://www.jscripter.org
JavaScript:
Re-compilers must redirect the resolution of the emulated original Java class or interface to this one.

int compareTo(T o)

Compares this object with the specified object for order.

Parameters:
o - A object to be compared.
Returns:
A negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as this object is less than, equal to, or greater than the specified object.
Throws:
java.io.ClassCastException - if the specified object's type prevents it from being compared to this object.
